<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>On Controller/Dispatcher/Standard.php around line 383 Zend_Controller_Exception is thrown if the module is not found. However if error plugin is used in the following fashion:</p>

<p>Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance()-&gt;registerPlugin(
            new Zend_Controller_Plugin_ErrorHandler(
                    array('module'=&gt;'errorhandler', 
                          'controller' =&gt; 'error', 
                          'action' =&gt; 'error')));</p>

<p>the only way to distinquish the module not found (404) from application error (500) is to check the error message. There are two possible solutions:</p>

<p>1) Throw Zend_Controller_Dispatcher_Exception in Controller/Dispatcher/Standard.php around line 383 instead of Zend_Controller_Exception</p>

<p>2) Add code 404 to the mentioned exception. this causes ErrorPlugin to set error type to EXCEPTION_NO_ACTION.</p>

